"""ICU ``Latin-ASCII`` transliteration table — GENERATED, do not edit by hand.

Maps every Unicode codepoint that ICU's ``Latin-ASCII`` transform rewrites to its ASCII
output. Codepoints ICU leaves unchanged are ABSENT (callers treat a miss as identity, so
the downstream non-alphanumeric step collapses them to a space — exactly as R does).

This is the ground truth behind
:func:`whep_digitize.general.helpers.strings.transliterate_ascii_lower`, replacing the
earlier ``anyascii``-plus-overrides approximation (the top migration parity risk).

Provenance: ``stringi::stri_trans_general(x, "Latin-ASCII")`` over the BMP + Mathematical
Alphanumeric Symbols, R 4.6.0 / stringi 1.8.7 / ICU 74.1 / Unicode 15.1. The mapping is
tied to that ICU version; regenerate against the R environment if it changes.
"""

